   The MK3 GOLF is officially 28 years old this year and it has become a legendary collector’s item. This iconic Volkswagen hatch employed a 2.8l engine which had a hypnotic sound equal to none. To date, the VR6 engine has become known as the go-to engine for those who want to apply more power to their MK1/Citi Golf hatch by doing an engine swap.  Fast Facts Volkswagen Golf VR6 Body: 5 door hatchback Drive: front wheels  Engine: 2792cc V6, SOHC, 12v  Power: 128kW @ 5800rpm  Torque: 235Nm @ 4200rpm  Transmission: 5-speed manual  0-100km/h: 7.6sec  